name.text: 15.2.2.5 y coord of COM of lamina by horizontal strips

questiontext.text:
Exercise

In this exercise we divide the lamina into a number of horizontal slices; a typical slice is shown below.

  1. In this case we will take a rectangle of width \(2 - x\) and height \(\delta y\). Find the mass \(m\) of this rectangle in term of \(\rho\) and \(y\).

    \(m=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]
    Enter rho for \(\rho\).

    The moment about the \(x\)-axis is then \(m\bar{y}\).

  2. We take the sum of all such moments and letting \(\delta \to 0\) we obtain the integral:

    \(\displaystyle{\int_{y=0}^{y=2}}\) [[input:ans5]]\(\textrm{d}y\)[[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt5]]

  3. Evaluate the integral above.

    [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]

  4.  Hence find \(\bar{y}=\)[[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]] [[feedback:prt6]]

generalfeedback.text:
1. \(\displaystyle (2 - x) \delta y, \rho (2 - x) \delta y, \rho (2 - x)y \delta y\)
  2. \(\displaystyle \int_{y=0}^{y=2} \rho (2 - y)y \textrm{d}y\)
  3. \(\displaystyle \frac{4 \rho}{3}\)
  4. As before the total mass is \(2 \rho\), and its moment about the \(x\)-axis is \(2 \rho \bar{y}\). Hence \( 2 \rho \bar{y} = \frac{4 \rho}{3}\) from which \(\bar{y} =\frac{2}{3}\) which was the result obtained in the previous exercise.
